  "prompt": "What is smart strategy to prepare for CMAT 2017?",
  "response": "Preparing for the CMAT (Common Management Admission Test) effectively requires a well-structured strategy. Here are some smart strategies to help you prepare for CMAT:\n\n### 1. Understand the Exam Pattern and Syllabus\n   - **Familiarize Yourself with the Format**: Understand the sections in CMAT, which typically include Quantitative Techniques & Data Interpretation, Logical Reasoning, Language Comprehension, and General Awareness.\n   - **Review the Syllabus**: Focus on the important topics within each section.\n\n### 2. Create a Study Plan\n   - **Set a Timeline**: Allocate specific time for each section, ensuring you cover the entire syllabus well before the exam date.\n   - **Daily Goals**: Set daily and weekly goals to keep track of your progress and stay motivated.\n\n### 3. Use Quality Study Material\n   - **Reference Books**: Choose the right books that cover CMAT topics comprehensively.\n   - **Online Resources**: Utilize online courses, video lectures, and quizzes for additional support.\n\n### 4. Practice Regularly\n   - **Mock Tests**: Take regular mock tests to get familiar with the exam format and time management.\n   - **Previous Year Papers**: Solve previous years\u2019 question papers to understand the type of questions asked.\n\n### 5. Focus on Weak Areas\n   - **Identify Weaknesses**: After mock tests, analyze your performance and identify areas where you need improvement.\n   - **Strengthen Fundamentals**: Go back to the basics for topics you find challenging.\n\n### 6. Revise and Review\n   - **Regular Revision**: Make it a point to revise regularly so that information remains fresh in your mind.\n   - **Short Notes**: Create concise notes for quick reviews before the exam.\n\n### 7. Time Management\n   - **Practice Under Time Constraints**: While practicing, simulate exam conditions to improve your speed and accuracy.\n   - **Prioritize Questions**: Learn to quickly identify which questions to tackle first based on your strengths.\n\n### 8. Stay Updated for General Awareness\n   - **Current Affairs**: Read newspapers, magazines, and online articles to stay updated on current events.\n   - **Static GK**: Include a section on static general knowledge in your study material.\n\n### 9. Work on Mental Fitness\n   - **Stay Healthy**: Maintain a balanced diet, exercise, and get sufficient sleep to keep your mind sharp.\n   - **Stress Management**: Practice meditation or relaxation techniques to manage exam stress.\n\n### 10. Join Study Groups or Classes\n   - **Collaborate with Peers**: Join study groups to share knowledge and resources.\n   - **Coaching Institutes**: If necessary, consider enrolling in coaching classes specializing in CMAT preparation.\n\n### 11. Stay Positive and Motivated\n   - **Stay Focused**: Keep your end goals in mind to stay motivated throughout your preparation.\n   - **Positive Affirmations**: Encourage yourself with positive thoughts and believe in your preparation.\n\nBy following these strategies, you can prepare effectively for the CMAT and enhance your chances of scoring well. Good luck with your preparation!",
